{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "In this strategy, the action is generated by extracting information from the agent memory according to the current task.",
    "The task and the extracted memories are used as prompts to trigger the agent actions.",
    "For example, in Generative Agents [20], the agent maintains a memory stream, and before taking each action, it retrieves recent, relevant and important information from the memory steam to guide the agent actions.",
    "In GITM [16], in order to achieve a low-level sub-goal, the agent queries its memory to determine if there are any successful experiences related to the task.",
    "If similar tasks have been completed previously, the agent invokes the previously successful actions to handle the current task directly."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "For example, in Generative Agents [20], the agent maintains a memory stream, and before taking each action, it retrieves recent, relevant and important information from the memory steam to guide the agent actions.",
    "In GITM [16], in order to achieve a low-level sub-goal, the agent queries its memory to determine if there are any successful experiences related to the task."
  ]
}